The '''Petroleum Price Board''' (''Petroleumsprisrådet'') is a Norwegian [[government agency]] responsible for setting norm prices for [[petroleum]] produced on the [[Norwegian continental shelf]]. The Board has six permanent members, including four government-appointed independent experts and one representative each from the [[Ministry of Finance (Norway)|Ministry of Finance]] and the [[Ministry of Petroleum and Energy (Norway)|Ministry of Petroleum and Energy]]. The Board meets quarterly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.npd.no/en/Regulations/Regulations/Norm-price-fixing/ |title=Regulations relating to norm price fixing - Norwegian Petroleum Directorate |publisher=Npd.no |date=2008-09-17 |accessdate=2012-03-17}}</ref>
